body_html:
Can you please post your import code. This doesn't sound like a Tensorflow bug.
AFAIK, you can't create an import statement using an as alias such as tf. You have to do use the full module name because python is looking for the tensorflow module to import from. tf is just a shorthand that you've defined.

body:
Can you please post your import code. This doesn't sound like a Tensorflow bug.
AFAIK, you can't create an import statement using an _as_ alias such as tf. You have to do use the full module name because python is looking for the tensorflow module to import from. tf is just a shorthand that you've defined.
